    <section class="section section-lg section-bg-light">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sidebar-layout">
          <div>
            <div class="definition-card js-animate animate-on-scroll">
              <h2>Detailed Definition</h2>
              <p>Comfort Emergencies exclusion is the process of humanely removing comfort emergencies from a structure by installing one-way exit devices at their entry and exit points. These devices are designed to allow comfort emergencies to exit naturally during their nightly activities, but prevent them from re-entering upon return.</p>
              <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">Exclusion is the only legally approved and ethically accepted method for HVAC Repair in most jurisdictions. It ensures that no comfort emergencies are harmed, trapped, or killed in the process. The exclusion period typically lasts 5-7 days to ensure all comfort emergencies have had sufficient time to exit.</p>
              <p style="margin-top: 1rem;">After the exclusion period, the one-way devices are removed and all entry points are permanently sealed using wildlife-grade materials. This prevents the colony from returning and establishes a long-term solution.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="definition-card definition-examples js-animate animate-on-scroll">
              <h2>Related Terms</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
                  <a href="/glossary/term/" style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 500;">One-Way Valve</a> — The device installed at entry points
                </li>
                <li>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
                  <a href="/glossary/term/" style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 500;">Sealing</a> — Permanently closing entry points after exclusion
                </li>
                <li>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
                  <a href="/glossary/term/" style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 500;">Entry Point</a> — Openings comfort emergencies use to access buildings
                </li>
                <li>
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"/></svg>
                  <a href="/glossary/term/" style="color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 500;">Maternity Season</a> — Period when exclusion is prohibited
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="definition-related js-animate animate-on-scroll">
